Distribution ( Fig. 49 ). An Eastern Mediterranean subpecies, known with certainty from Albania , Bosnia , Bulgaria , Croatia (Dalmatia), Greece and some Greek islands (except Crete ), Macedonia , Montenegro , Serbia , western and northern Turkey (where, in some provinces, it is sympatric with N . s .
stearinus
). Historical data exists for westerly areas beyond the range stated above ( Baleares , Sardinia, Sicily, Spain ) which, like the old specimen examined in BMNH labelled " France ", might be the result of misidentification and/or mislabelling.
